<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?>

<exploration xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xml:id="oa-5-2-percent-decrease">
    <statement>
        <p>
            Sales and discounts are an everyday example of percent decreases. For example, if you sign up for an online store's mailing list, you will receive a coupon for 15% <em>off</em> one item. 
        </p>
        <ol marker="(a)">
            <li>
                <p>
                    If the item's original price was $21.95, how much is your discount?
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    What is the final purchase price of the item? (Hint: subtract.)
                </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    Can you think of a <xref ref="ss-2-2-one-step" text="custom">one-step process</xref> for finding the final purchase price of the item? Explain your thinking.
                </p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </statement>
</exploration>